.SH "NAME"
.IX Header "NAME"
Pod::Text \- convert POD data to formatted ASCII text
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        use Pod::Text;
.Ve
.Vb 1
\&        pod2text("perlfunc.pod");
.Ve
Also:
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        pod2text < input.pod
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Pod::Text is a module that can convert documentation in the POD format (such
as can be found throughout the Perl distribution) into formatted ASCII.
Termcap is optionally supported for boldface/underline, and can enabled via
\f(CW$Pod::Text::termcap=1\fR. If termcap has not been enabled, then backspaces
will be used to simulate bold and underlined text.
.PP
A separate \fIpod2text\fR program is included that is primarily a wrapper for
Pod::Text.
.PP
The single function \f(CWpod2text()\fR can take one or two arguments. The first
should be the name of a file to read the pod from, or \*(L"<&STDIN\*(R" to read from
STDIN. A second argument, if provided, should be a filehandle glob where
output should be sent.
